      <div xml:id="NA335-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu kāmamikka kaḻipaṭar kiḷavi mītūrntu talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said dejectedly with a word of utmost affliction when passion had increased.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA335">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            tiṅkaḷun tikaḻvā ṉērtarum miḷanīrp</l>
<l>            poṅkutiraip puṇariyum pāṭō vātē</l>
<l>            yoliciṟan tōtamum peyaru malipuṉaṟ</l>
<l>            palpūṅ kāṉaṉ muḷḷilait tāḻai</l>
<l>            cōṟucori kuṭaiyiṟ kūmpumukai yaviḻa</l>
<l>            vaḷiparan tūṭṭum viḷivi ṉāṟṟamoṭu</l>
<l>            maiyirum paṉaimicaip paitala vuyavu</l>
<l>            maṉṟilu meṉpuṟa naralu maṉṟiv</l>
<l>            viralkavarn tuḻanta kavarvi ṉalyāḻ</l>
<l>            yāma muyyāmai niṉṟatu</l>
<l>            kāmam peritē kaḷaiñarō vilarē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The moon is rising in the glittering sky, and the ocean</l>
<l>with [its] foaming waves of young water does not stop singing.</l>
<l rend="indent3">Apart from the Aṉṟil, too, calling in my back,</l>
<l rend="indent">suffering [its] miseries(?) high on the collyrium-dark palmyra tree</l>
<l rend="indent2">with undestructable fragrance that feeds [me], the wind spreading [it],</l>
<l rend="indent3">while the closed buds open, like cups from which rice is poured forth,</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the Tāḻai trees with thorny leaves in the many-flowered seashore</l>
<l rend="indent2">grove, in the increasing torrent, as the flood, too, moves in,</l>
<l rend="indent2">overwhelming in sound,</l>
<l>the good lute sweet with desire, skilfully(?) seized by fingers,</l>
<l>lingers, unescapable(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">uyyāmai</term>: we would like parallels for this strange use of the negative abstract noun.</note> at midnight.</l>
<l>Desire [is] great. Ah, no one there to remove [it].</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
